==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Log-chip
<hw>Log"-chip`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>A thin, flat piece of board in the form of a quadrant of a circle
attached to the log line; -- called also <altname>log-ship</altname>.
See 2d <er>Log</er>, <pos>n.</pos>, 2.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Logcock</ent>⟦br⟧
